Barclays Wealth Appoints 12 Senior Bankers, Advisers in Asia

-- B y   K y u n g h e e   P a r k
-- 
2011-03-28T03:26:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-28/barclays-wealth-appoints-12-senior-bankers-advisers-in-asia.html
Barclays Plc (BARC) â€™s wealth unit
appointed 12 director-level private bankers and investment
advisers in  Singapore  and Hong Kong in the first quarter to
expand its business serving wealthy clients in Asia.  Nine were hired in Singapore and three in Hong Kong, the
company said in an e-mailed statement today.  In Singapore, Benjamin Yeo was hired from Bank of Singapore
as head of Asia research, economics and strategy. Eddie Tan,
formerly of JPMorgan Private Bank, and Lim Ming How from Credit
Suisse Private Bank joined the Singapore/Malaysia private
banking team. Kirk Tan was appointed director of credit
structuring and was previously at Citi Private Bank.  Also in Singapore, Amrit Uppal, formerly of Credit Suisse
in the U.K., was named a director of the South  Asia  private
banking team, as were Mustafa Mahmood, previously of Goldman
Sachs, and Nakul Beri from Barclays Wealth in India. Sara Mi was
hired from  HSBC Private Bank  as a director on the Southeast Asia
active advisory team. Michelle Le Herissier was appointed as
head of Barclays Wealth Trustees (Singapore) Ltd. and came from
Cititrust.  Barbara Yenson was hired from RBS Coutts on the Hong Kong
private banking team and Sonia Lee, formerly at Natixis Asia,
was appointed as a director on the North Asia active advisory
group. Joanna Ho, previously at HSBC Private Bank, was named
head of North Asia wealth advisory.  The appointments were reported earlier today by the
Business Times.  To contact the reporter on this story:
